To compile the library:
 mkdir build
 cd build
 cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="your path to LLVM and Z3 cmake config" \
       -DCMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH="your path to grpc, protobuf include dir" ..
 make

Note that the reason why we need to use the above flags are:
 1. -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH is to facilitate our cmake to locate package 
    for LLVM and Z3. 
 2. -DCMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH is to locate the include file for grpc and protobuf.
    It seems that there's no instrinsic macro defined in their cmake config for
    include file so that we have to manually define.

Dependent library: LLVM and Z3 SAT Solver
Please add cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="your path to LLVM and Z3" ..

Doing so will generate a binary called
static-analysis

We can also compile using Ninja by setting compile generator to Ninja during cmake
  cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="your path to LLVM and Z3" -G Ninja ..
Then to compile the project, simply run Ninja (Note, please install Ninja by
apt install ninja-build)
  ninja